news.title: Gujarat government clears major hurdles for redevelopment of old societies
news.para: Though the existing amendment to the Gujarat Ownership Flats Act (1972) was made in September 2018, it was in December 2019 that the urban development department clearly stated that the redevelopment clause also applies to housing societies governed by Gujarat Cooperatives Act.

news.title: DDA reopens land pooling portal, hopes for better response
news.para: “The response has been positive and the aim of reopening the portal from November 10 to December 24 is to allow more participation. Those who have land parcels near the priority sectors will particularly benefit from this opportunity,” said a DDA official.

news.title: Rise in construction material, labour cost may push up realty rates in Kolkata
news.para: The increase will be around 15 per cent in the affordable segment till 2022, which will translate to Rs 450 to Rs 1000 per sq feet considering the price bracket for it is Rs 3000 to Rs 6000 per square ft, a CREDAI official said.

news.title: Reliance Home Finance posts net loss of Rs 284.49 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Reliance Home Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 70.76 crore in Q2 FY22, a dip of 73 per cent from Rs 259.11 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's net profit up 35% to Rs 15.25 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 142.41 crore in Q2 FY22, a dip of from Rs 152.33 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Avenue Supermarts buys retail space in Bengaluru
news.para: Avenue Supermarts, which owns DMart stores, has purchased a total of 67,000 square feet in Hobli, Varthur, which covers three floors and includes 135 parking spaces, according to real estate data and analytics platform Propstack.

news.title: Saya Homes acquires stalled commercial project in Noida
news.para: The commercial project with development potential of 1.3 million sq ft, will be completed in three years, said Vikas Bhasin, managing director of NCR-based Saya Homes.

news.title: Migsun acquires HDFC's stake in Greater Noida's SEZ project
news.para: Last year, the group had acquired Ansal's stake in Ansal IT City Park (SEZ) Tech Zone. Migsun Group will now have 100 per cent stake after acquiring HDFC's 37% stake and the rest of Ansal API.

news.title: ASK Property Investment Advisors invests Rs 215 crore in Mahagun's Noida project
news.para: The project located in sector 107 of Noida will be constructed on a 10-acre land parcel, which has a potential of developing a saleable area of over 2 million sq ft comprising low-rise and high-rise apartments.

news.title: HCC posts net profit of Rs 139 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Hindustan Construction Company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,848.20 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 56 per cent from Rs 1,831.10 crore in Q2 FY21.

news.title: Evergrande dodges default again; property sector debt concerns linger
news.para: Evergrande, the world's most indebted developer, has been stumbling from deadline to deadline in recent weeks as it grapples with more than $300 billion in liabilities, $19 billion of which are dollar bonds.

news.title: Piramal Enterprises' net profit dips 32% to Rs 426 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Consolidated revenue from operations stood at Rs 3,105.52 crore for the quarter under consideration. It was Rs 3,301.84 crore for the same period a year ago, Piramal Enterprises added.

news.title: Delhi government forms fifth MVC to give recommendations to civic bodies
news.para: According to civic officials, the primary task of MVC-5 will be to make recommendations to the three civic bodies on matters relating to increase or decrease in rates of property tax on residential as well as commercial and rented properties.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises posts net loss of Rs 13.65 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Brigade Enterprises' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 776.08 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 141 per cent from Rs 322.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: HomeFirst Finance appoints Dharmvir Singh as CTO & Ashishkumar Darji as CRO
news.para: Singh has an experience of over 15 years with his last assignment being with Hero Fincorp. Prior to joining Home First, Darji was technical director at KPMG.
